terms.medium_def:
A prophet from the tribe of Levi living at the time of United Monarchy, first mentioned at 1Sa.1.20; 
referred to as Samuel or Samuel (KJV= Shemuel) (שְׁמוּאֵל), or Samuel (Σαμουήλ); 
a son of Elkanah and Hannah; 
father of Joel and Abijah.

A man living at the time of the Patriarchs, first mentioned at Gen.5.32; 
referred to as Shem (שֵׁם), or Shem (KJV= Sem) (Σήμ); 
son of Noah; 
a brother of Ham and Japheth; 
father of Asshur, Elam, Arpachshad, Lud and Aram. § the eldest son of Noah and progenitor of the Semitic tribes

A man from the tribe of Manasseh living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, first mentioned at Num.26.32; 
referred to as Shemida (שְׁמִידָ֑ע), or Shemidaite (שְׁמִידָעִי); 
son of Gilead; 
a brother of Abiezer, Helek, Asriel, Shechem and Hepher; 
father of Ahian, Shechem, Likhi and Aniam. § a son of Gilead, grandson of Manasseh, and progenitor of a family in Manasseh

A man living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, only mentioned at Num.34.20; 
only referred to as Shemuel (שְׁמוּאֵל); 
a son of Ammihud.

A man from the tribe of Issachar living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, only mentioned at 1Ch.7.2; 
only referred to as Shemuel (שְׁמוּאֵל); 
son of Tola; 
a brother of Uzzi, Rephaiah, Jeriel, Jahmai and Ibsam.

A man from the tribe of Manasseh living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, first mentioned at Num.26.32; 
referred to as Shemida (שְׁמִידָ֑ע), or Shemidaite (שְׁמִידָעִי); 
son of Gilead; 
a brother of Abiezer, Helek, Asriel, Shechem and Hepher; 
father of Ahian, Shechem, Likhi and Aniam. § Shemidaites, of Shemida "wise"
descendants of Shemida, the son of Gilead and grandson of Manasseh
